QUALIFICATION: Isotoma pritchardi was transferred to the genus Halisotoma by Bagnall, R.S. 1949. Contributions towards a knowledge of the Isotomidae (Collembola). VII-XV. Annals and Magazine of Natural History 12 2: 82-96 solely on the basis of Womersley's original description and without Bagnall examining types of the species; the diagnostic character, however, for Halisotoma was not mentioned by Womersley in his description (presence of two spatulate and apically fringed setae distally and externally on tibiotarsus II) and this character has not been observed on the syntype in the SAMA or on adult females and males from other localities; consequently this species may correctly belong in Isotoma sensu stricto

AUTHOR: Bagnall

PUB_PUB_PARENT_JOURNAL_TITLE: Annals and Magazine of Natural History
PUB_PUB_FORMATTED: Bagnall, R.S. 1949. Contributions towards a knowledge of the Isotomidae (Collembola). VII-XV. Annals and Magazine of Natural History 12 2: 82-96

QUALIFICATION: Womersley listed 'holotype and allotype' in his original description and stated that the types were in the SAMA; it is clear from the description that he had both the male and a female before him when describing the species and he mentions no other material; the SAMA collection contains two specimens of this species on the same slide labelled: 'types a & b' on one label, and 'Isotoma swani n.sp. & Nat. Pk. WA 3.9.31 DCS det. H. Womersley' on another label; there is no indication of whether the male or female is the holotype; the female is here selected as the holotype and the male as the paratype; both specimens possess short, smooth spines in a single row on the dens, a character not mentioned by Womersley and in this and other respects they resemble a species of Setocerura Salmon, 1949, see Greenslade, Penelope 1989. Genera of Isotomidae with spined dentes from southern regions. pp. 107-118 in Dallai, R. (ed). Third International Seminar on Apterygota. Sienna : University of Sienna; Australotoma Bagnall, 1949 therefore may be a senior subjective synonym of Setocerura Salmon, 1949

QUALIFICATION: according to Ellis & Bellinger op. cit. Salmon's original description of the genus is invalid since he cited no type species; Salmon is quoted as the authority for the genus where a type species, Odontella minutissima Salmon, 1941 is cited (not Zealandella minutissima as quoted by Salmon); unfortunately, Salmon (op. cit. p. 250) gives Zealandella minutadenta as the type species, a species he determined (p. 111) as Xenylla novazealandia Salmon, 1941; (Xenylla novazealandia was later synonymised with Xenylla maritima, see Gama Assalino, M.M. & Greenslade, Penelope 1981. Relationships between the distribution and phylogeny of Xenylla (Collembola: Hypogastruridae) species in Australia and New Zealand. Revue d'Écologie et de Biologie du Sol 18(2): 269-284); Salmon (op. cit. p. 111) synonymised Clavontella caerulea Salmon, 1944 with Zealandella minutissima (or in reality Odontella minutissima); they are type species for the genera Clavontella Salmon, 1944 and Zealandella Salmon, 1964 respectively; Salmon (op. cit.) says Zealandella has priority not Clavontella Salmon, 1944 but following ICZN Art. 13b this is not so, hence Zealandella is a junior synonym of Clavontella Salmon, 1944; Deharveng, L. 1981. La famille des Odontellidae: phylogénèse et taxonomie. Trav. Lab. d'Ecobiol. Arthr. Edaphiques Toulouse 3(1): 1-21 synonymised Zealandella with Odontella Schäffer, 1897 and included Clavontella also; Clavontella caerulea Salmon, 1944 and Odontella minutissima Salmon, 1941 may represent two valid species of Odontella Schäffer, 1897
